{"id":32643,"title":"Endoplasmic reticulum calcium, stress, and cell-to-cell adhesion.","abstract":"Darier's disease (DD) is caused by mutations in the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) Ca2+ ATPase ATP2A2 (protein SERCA2). Current treatment modalities are ineffective for many patients. This report shows that impaired SERCA2 function, both in DD keratinocytes and in normal keratinocytes treated with the SERCA2-inhibitor thapsigargin, depletes ER Ca2+ stores, leading to constitutive ER stress and increased sensitivity to ER stressors. ER stress, in turn, leads to abnormal cell-to-cell adhesion via impaired redistribution of desmoplakin, desmoglein 3, desmocollin 3, and E-cadherin to the plasma membrane. This report illustrates how ER Ca2+ depletion and the resulting ER stress are central to the pathogenesis of the disease. Additionally, the authors introduce a possible new therapeutic agent, miglustat.","date":"2014-06-13","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24924761","annotations":[{"name":"Endoplasmic reticulum","weight":0.893958,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endoplasmic_reticulum"},{"name":"Calcium","weight":0.829999,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calcium"},{"name":"Protein","weight":0.829773,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Protein"},{"name":"Cell membrane","weight":0.808183,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell_membrane"},{"name":"Adenosine triphosphate","weight":0.785599,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adenosine_triphosphate"},{"name":"Keratinocyte","weight":0.681613,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keratinocyte"},{"name":"Mutation","weight":0.610086,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mutation"},{"name":"Blood plasma","weight":0.451706,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_plasma"},{"name":"Cell adhesion","weight":0.430491,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell_adhesion"},{"name":"ATPase","weight":0.421364,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ATPase"},{"name":"ATP2A2","weight":0.393634,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ATP2A2"},{"name":"Enzyme inhibitor","weight":0.338413,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enzyme_inhibitor"},{"name":"Biological membrane","weight":0.336595,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biological_membrane"},{"name":"Pathogenesis","weight":0.282576,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathogenesis"},{"name":"Stress (biology)","weight":0.229465,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stress_(biology)"},{"name":"SERCA","weight":0.213142,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SERCA"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.210873,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Desmoplakin","weight":0.12873,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Desmoplakin"},{"name":"Receptor (biochemistry)","weight":0.102966,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Receptor_(biochemistry)"},{"name":"Sensitivity and specificity","weight":0.070554,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sensitivity_and_specificity"},{"name":"Thapsigargin","weight":0.062063,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thapsigargin"},{"name":"Desmoglein","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Desmoglein"},{"name":"Desmoglein 3","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Desmoglein_3"},{"name":"Unfolded protein response","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unfolded_protein_response"},{"name":"Miglustat","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miglustat"},{"name":"Desmocollin","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Desmocollin"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.0227187,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therap